== Bracketbot and Referencebot are welcoming vandals ==

I'm not sure whether this is appropriate for a bugzilla report, hence this entry here, but wikipedia's behaviour is not ideal. In [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Conquistador&diff=607444267&oldid=607417328 this edit], a vandal removed a random chunk of code, without citations, so perhaps Cluebot wouldn't notice such a thing. In any case, Bracketbot's response to this on the [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk:123.211.40.198&diff=607485588&oldid=607444962 IP's talk page] is a bit absurd. Similarly, [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk:24.181.27.86&oldid=607259239 Referencebot] has welcomed a vandal with open arms in response to a seriously scrambled [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?diff=607219249 edit] that involved, inter alia, deleting all the references from the page. Could these bots be asked to run a bit less enthusiastically? [[User:Sminthopsis84|Sminthopsis84]] ([[User talk:Sminthopsis84|talk]]) 15:01, 7 May 2014 (UTC)

:I think such things are usually raised at the bot's/bot's owner's TP? '''[[User:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#060">It Is Me Here</span>]]''' <sup>'''[[User_talk:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">t</span>]] / [[Special:Contribs/It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">c</span>]]'''</sup> 09:42, 10 May 2014 (UTC)

