== Tables and other multimedia objects ==

Tables cannot be put under other multimedia objects. See [[User:Esszet/sandbox/tableissue|here]] for an example. [[User:Esszet|Esszet]] ([[User talk:Esszet|talk]]) 10:42, 8 May 2014 (UTC)

:I don't think a table is considered a multimedia object. <code>class="wikitable floatright"</code> will place it below the image in your example. [[User:PrimeHunter|PrimeHunter]] ([[User talk:PrimeHunter|talk]]) 11:19, 8 May 2014 (UTC)

::Ah. Thank you. [[User:Esszet|Esszet]] ([[User talk:Esszet|talk]]) 13:51, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::Yes, align only says something about position. Multimedia objects also automatically "clear" (so go on the next line from a previous right floating element), but tables do not. So you either need to manually (<code>style="clear:right"</code>) or you use the <code>floatright</code> class, which aligns and clears at the same time. —[[User:TheDJ|Th<span style="color: green">e</span>DJ]] ([[User talk:TheDJ|talk]] • [[Special:Contributions/TheDJ|contribs]]) 07:51, 9 May 2014 (UTC)

== Section links not working properly ==

Normally when I click on a link to a particular section of a page, I'm brought to that section. However, for the past few days I've noticed that while I am brought to the section while the page is loading, once loading is complete it jumps back up to the top of the page. How can I fix this? [[User:Nikkimaria|Nikkimaria]] ([[User talk:Nikkimaria|talk]]) 12:09, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:Do you use [[WP:WikEd]]?  I've been havng the same problem and it only went away when I disabled WikEd (logged as an issue at [[User talk:Cacycle/wikEd]]), having tried every other gadget and script I'd got installed. [[User:Nthep|Nthep]] ([[User talk:Nthep|talk]]) 12:47, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::I've noticed that problem. I did have WikEd, but disabled it. Still happens.[[User:Sphilbrick|<span style="color:#002868;padding:0 4px;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">S Philbrick</span>]][[User talk:Sphilbrick|<span style=";padding:0 4px;color:# 000;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">(Talk)</span>]] 15:57, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::I've just blanked my common.js, common.css and gone through each entry there and all the gadgets in preferences that I have enabled and the problem for me seems to be when both WikEd and HotCat are enabled.  Disable one or the other and I have no problem. [[User:Nthep|Nthep]] ([[User talk:Nthep|talk]]) 16:06, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::: Oops, I was mistaken. I thought I recently disabled WikEd, but it was the enhanced tool bar I disabled. I just disabled WikEd, and that "solved" the problem.--[[User:Sphilbrick|<span style="color:#002868;padding:0 4px;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">S Philbrick</span>]][[User talk:Sphilbrick|<span style=";padding:0 4px;color:# 000;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">(Talk)</span>]] 16:26, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
: Can anybody get HotCat to work? I do nopt see the jumping problems, but I also do not see anything HotCat related on my edit pages (independent of wikEd enabled or not). [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]] ([[User talk:Cacycle|talk]]) 18:56, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::HotCat works but when both it and WikED are enabled this bouncing behaviour is seen, diable either and problem goes away.  Looking at [[c:MediaWiki:Gadget-HotCat.js]] HotCat was upgraded to v2.28 last weekend which was when I first saw the problem, whether this has anything to do with it I don't know. [[User:Nthep|Nthep]] ([[User talk:Nthep|talk]]) 09:00, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
:::No, HotCat's upgrade to 2.28 cannot possibly have anything to do with this. (Famous last words... :-) That upgrade just affected the behavior of the category editor, which opens after a user clicked the (±) or (+) link, and only if the user uses an IME (Input method editor). Other behavior of HotCat has not changed. However, I see quite a lot of recent [{{fullurl:User:Cacycle/wikEd.js|action=history}} changes in wikEd].
:::Anyway, if you want anybody to be able to try to reproduce the problem, we need more information: which browser are you using? Firefox/Safari/Chrome/Opera/IE? On which OS? Which versions (of both)? Does the problem appear on all pages? Or only on some? Can you give us a section link that does consistently lead to the problem you mention? Are there any JavaScript-related error messages in your browser's error log/console? If so, what do they say? [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 20:34, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::::Firefox 29.0.1, Windows 8.1 (by had same issue on Firefox 17/Windows XP, IE11/Windows8.1), Modern skin (but also seen the same problem using Vector and Monobook).  The issue occurs whenever I click on any section link on any page e.g. from watchlist or article history and I can't see any js related errors in Firefox's console. [[User:Nthep|Nthep]] ([[User talk:Nthep|talk]]) 21:05, 9 May 2014 (UTC)

:It's line 3648 in wikEd, which does <code>window.scroll(0, wikEd.GetOffsetTop(wikEd.inputWrapper) - 2);</code>. That's inside <code>wikEd.TurnOn()</code>, and it makes the page jump to the top. [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 21:19, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::Hm. WikEd looks for an edit form (elements #editform, wpTextarea1 etc) in the DOM, and if it finds one, assumes it's on an edit page. HotCat does add a similar hidden form to make its edits (but the form id is #hotcatCommitForm, not #editform like for normal edit pages). So, when both are active, depending on the order the scripts run, it may or may not work: if wikEd runs first, the HotCat form isn't there yet, and everything is fine. If HotCat runs first, wikEd is misled, and then the "jump to top" problem occurs. Now, that's an area of HotCat that hasn't changed in a long time, and although I'm not sure, I don't think wikEd has changed in that area either. Why didn't that problem surface earlier? [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]], any suggestions for avoiding this conflict? [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 21:47, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::: Thanks for these details. I will check into it. [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]] ([[User talk:Cacycle|talk]]) 21:52, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::::BTW: if there ''is'' an element with id "hotcatCommitForm" in the DOM, you can be sure not to be on an edit page, as HotCat is never active on edit pages. [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 22:34, 9 May 2014 (UTC)

::::: I have fixed the problem in the current version 0.9.126b, please update with Shift-Reload. Thanks to [[User:Lupo|Lupo]]! [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]] ([[User talk:Cacycle|talk]]) 22:57, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
:::::: OK, not yet fixed but still working on it... [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]] ([[User talk:Cacycle|talk]]) 23:10, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::::::: Finally it works... (wikEd version 0.9.126c). [[User:Cacycle|Cacycle]] ([[User talk:Cacycle|talk]]) 23:30, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::::::::Thank you both for investigating and resolving this. [[User:Nthep|Nthep]] ([[User talk:Nthep|talk]]) 10:29, 10 May 2014 (UTC)

== How to search through User history? ==

I want to search through user edit history for specific articles, every time I use the Tag filter in contributions no results appear even when I know the user edited the article. [[User:Valoem|<font color="DarkSlateGray">'''Valoem'''</font>]] <sup>[[User talk:Valoem|'''<font color="blue">talk</font>''']]</sup> <sup>[[Special:Contributions/Valoem|'''<font color="Green">contrib</font>''']]</sup> 15:06, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:The [[Special:Tags|tag filter]] looks for articles that match certain defined criteria, like a section being blanked. If you want to see all the edits made by one specific user to one specific article, you can either go to their contribs and search for the article, or go to the article history and search for the username. In both cases, leave the tag filter window empty. --[[User:Redrose64|<span style="color:#a80000; background:#ffeeee; text-decoration:inherit">Red</span>rose64]] ([[User talk:Redrose64|talk]]) 16:32, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::So I have to manually search through all contribs? [[User:Valoem|<font color="DarkSlateGray">'''Valoem'''</font>]] <sup>[[User talk:Valoem|'''<font color="blue">talk</font>''']]</sup> <sup>[[Special:Contributions/Valoem|'''<font color="Green">contrib</font>''']]</sup> 17:12, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::Or the articles' history. There are other things you can do. Most useful is try and narrow it down by date to shorten either sort of list. Sometimes 'what links here' helps if it e.g. finds a related formal discussion, such as an RM or AfD, or an archive such as for a notice board, all of which will have dates on. Or the articles' talk pages which again have dated contributions.--<small>[[User:JohnBlackburne|JohnBlackburne]]</small><sup>[[User_talk:JohnBlackburne|words]]</sup><sub style="margin-left:-2.0ex;">[[Special:Contributions/JohnBlackburne|deeds]]</sub> 17:30, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:{{reply to|Valoem}} You could use [[commons:MediaWiki:Gadget-rightsfilter.js]] in [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Contributions&offset=20150101000000&limit=250&tagfilter=&contribs=user&target=Valoem&namespace=0&lifilter=1&lifilterexpr=outer+space the user contributions page]. [[User:Helder.wiki|Helder.wiki]] 19:35, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::Sorry, how do I do this? [[User:Valoem|<font color="DarkSlateGray">'''Valoem'''</font>]] <sup>[[User talk:Valoem|'''<font color="blue">talk</font>''']]</sup> <sup>[[Special:Contributions/Valoem|'''<font color="Green">contrib</font>''']]</sup> 20:02, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::{{reply to|JohnBlackburne}} You just need to add<blockquote><syntaxhighlight lang="javascript" enclose="none">
mw.loader.load( '//commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=MediaWiki:Gadget-rightsfilter.js&action=raw&ctype=text/javascript&smaxage=21600&maxage=86400' );</syntaxhighlight></blockquote> to [[Special:MyPage/common.js|your common.js]] (and [[Wikipedia:Bypass your cache|clear you cache]]). [[User:Helder.wiki|Helder.wiki]] 20:39, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::::Added and clear cache now what? [[User:Valoem|<font color="DarkSlateGray">'''Valoem'''</font>]] <sup>[[User talk:Valoem|'''<font color="blue">talk</font>''']]</sup> <sup>[[Special:Contributions/Valoem|'''<font color="Green">contrib</font>''']]</sup> 21:10, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:::::{{reply to|Valoem}} check [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Contributions&offset=20150101000000&limit=250&tagfilter=&contribs=user&target=Valoem&namespace=0&lifilter=1&lifilterexpr=outer+space the link] I posted above. There will be a new field where you can type something, and the script will restrict the list to (or highlight) those items which match what you choose. [[User:Helder.wiki|Helder.wiki]] 22:08, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
::::::...and on other [[Special:SpecialPages|special pages]] where there are lists, check the action menu in the top of the page to find a "Filter" link which shows this field. [[User:Helder.wiki|Helder.wiki]] 22:10, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:{{reply to|Valoem}} You might also find the [https://tools.wmflabs.org/usersearch/ user contribution search] tool useful. '''[[User:Graham87|Graham]]'''<font color="green">[[User talk:Graham87|87]]</font> 08:45, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
::{{reply to|Graham87}} The tool doesn't seem to load for me. [[User:Valoem|<font color="DarkSlateGray">'''Valoem'''</font>]] <sup>[[User talk:Valoem|'''<font color="blue">talk</font>''']]</sup> <sup>[[Special:Contributions/Valoem|'''<font color="Green">contrib</font>''']]</sup> 13:25, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
:::It's working for me at the moment, but the WMF Labs server is flaky. '''[[User:Graham87|Graham]]'''<font color="green">[[User talk:Graham87|87]]</font> 14:35, 9 May 2014 (UTC)

== Reduced pull quote problem ==

The template {{tl|Reduced pull quote}} is supposed to display curly quotes, then the selected text rendered in Times New Roman with size 3.3 em. It clearly is not—the quotes are there, but it looks like the standard font. (I asked this question on the template talk page, but that page doesn't get much traffic so asking here.)[[User:Sphilbrick|<span style="color:#002868;padding:0 4px;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">S Philbrick</span>]][[User talk:Sphilbrick|<span style=";padding:0 4px;color:# 000;font-family: Copperplate Gothic Light">(Talk)</span>]] 15:46, 8 May 2014 (UTC)

== attempt to move a move-protected page by non-admin results in wrong error message ==
{{tracked|40145}}
About a year and a half ago, I reported a bug in which MediaWiki displays the wrong message error when a non-admin tries to move a move-protected page ({{Bugzilla|40145}}); the message would say the page can only be edited by admins even when it's merely protected from moves. A developer reported that the bug has been fixed, but when I try to rename a move-protected page with my non-admin test account, it still says the page can only be edited by administrators.

Does one of the system messages need to be updated, or is this some sort of regression? --[[User:Ixfd64|Ixfd64]] ([[User talk:Ixfd64|talk]]) 17:34, 8 May 2014 (UTC)
:I've reopened the bug, and I have a patch now. The problem is that we customize the message that they changed, and we can't currently tell whether it's being called for an edit or move. My patch will allow it to distinguish these cases. [[User:Jackmcbarn|Jackmcbarn]] ([[User talk:Jackmcbarn|talk]]) 19:25, 8 May 2014 (UTC)

