== Sort-table sorting numbers "alphabetically" ==
{{resolved}}
The table at [[:Casualties_of_the_Syrian_Civil_War#Foreign_civilians_killed]] seems to be sorting the second, numerical column "alphabetically" (''e''.''g''. 11 ... 19 ... 2 ...). Could anyone help? Thanks! '''[[User:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#060">It Is Me Here</span>]]''' <sup>'''[[User_talk:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">t</span>]] / [[Special:Contribs/It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">c</span>]]'''</sup> 17:17, 12 May 2014 (UTC)
: {{re|It Is Me Here}} Yes[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Casualties_of_the_Syrian_Civil_War&diff=608252918&oldid=608249851]. The table sorter does try to detect table columns containing only numeric values, but this fails in some cases (the problem here are the references, a value like "74[110]" is nor recognizable as a number). [[User:Matma Rex|Matma Rex]] <small>[[User talk:Matma Rex|talk]]</small> 17:39, 12 May 2014 (UTC)
::{{Thank you}}! '''[[User:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#060">It Is Me Here</span>]]''' <sup>'''[[User_talk:It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">t</span>]] / [[Special:Contribs/It Is Me Here|<span style="color:#C60">c</span>]]'''</sup> 19:28, 12 May 2014 (UTC)

