== Inline audio ==

{{tl|Audio-nohelp}} allows text to be linked inline to an audio file.  Unfortunately, clicking the link opens the file player in the full window.  Is there a template that will just play the sound without leaving the article page, or at worst, in a pop-up window? There is particularly a problem in the tables at [[Morse code#Letters, numbers, punctuation]].  It is quite inconvenient to have to keep backing out of the file player while trying to read through the tables and listen at the same time. '''[[User:Spinningspark|<font style="background:#fafad2;color:#C08000">Spinning</font>]][[User talk:Spinningspark|<font style="color:#4840a0">Spark</font>]]''' 10:26, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
:: I saw that,  and [[Template:Audio]] does pretty much the same thing.  Something along the lines of [[Template:Listen]] might be better as it would allow you to stay on the same page. For example:
{{Listen
| filename    = Accordion chords-01.ogg
| title       = Accordion chords
| pos         = left
| description = Chords being played on an accordion
}}{{clear}}
::Runs just fine on this same page.  It's a bit more coding tho!  [[User talk:KoshVorlon|<span style="background-color:royalblue;padding:4px;color:lightgrey;text-shadow:black 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em"><b>''K''osh''V''orlon&nbsp;&nbsp; ''Angeli i demoni kruzhili nado mnoj'' </b></span>]]'' 16:48, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
:::Did you look at the tables I linked? Multiple instances of a sound player graphic are not really going to work. '''[[User:Spinningspark|<font style="background:#fafad2;color:#C08000">Spinning</font>]][[User talk:Spinningspark|<font style="color:#4840a0">Spark</font>]]''' 16:51, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
:::: I saw it.   Check the [[Template:Listen]] page as they have a plain example too: 
{{Listen
| filename = Accordion chords-01.ogg
| title    = Accordion chords
| plain    = yes
| style    = float:right
}}
::::[[User talk:KoshVorlon|<span style="background-color:royalblue;padding:4px;color:lightgrey;text-shadow:black 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em"><b>''K''osh''V''orlon&nbsp;&nbsp; ''Angeli i demoni kruzhili nado mnoj'' </b></span>]]'' 16:56, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
::::[[User:Spinningspark | Spinningspark ]]  I just cobled this together in my sandbox,  how about something like this.  (Plain box with a play button, it plays on the page itself, and it still fits within the tabled setup on Morse Code page:
{| class="wikitable sortable" style="float:right; margin:1em"
|-
! Character || Code || Sound File
|-
| [[A|A, a]] || <center> '''·&nbsp;–''' </center> || {{Listen|filename = A morse code.ogg|plain = yes| style=float:right}} 
|-
| [[B|B, b]] || <center> '''–&nbsp;·&nbsp;·&nbsp;·''' || {{Listen|filename = B morse code.ogg|plain = yes| style=float:right}}   
|-
|}
::::[[User talk:KoshVorlon|<span style="background-color:royalblue;padding:4px;color:lightgrey;text-shadow:black 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em"><b>''K''osh''V''orlon&nbsp;&nbsp; ''Angeli i demoni kruzhili nado mnoj'' </b></span>]]'' 17:57, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
::::: That's a lot better in my opinion, but it it's going to make the table a lot wider.  I was hoping to preserve just the linking of the audio from the code. '''[[User:Spinningspark|<font style="background:#fafad2;color:#C08000">Spinning</font>]][[User talk:Spinningspark|<font style="color:#4840a0">Spark</font>]]''' 18:20, 13 May 2014 (UTC)
