== Redirect not working right ==
{{tracked|65468}}
The target of the redirect [[WP:NMOTORSPORT]] is, as it should be, [[Wikipedia:Notability (sports)#Motorsports]]; but clicking on it doesn't take you to the right place in the article. Any ideas? [[User:JohnCD|JohnCD]] ([[User talk:JohnCD|talk]]) 20:28, 7 May 2014 (UTC)
:It works for me, using Firefox 28. Some browsers may get confused by the collapsed "FAQ" box at the top of the page. -- [[User:John of Reading|John of Reading]] ([[User talk:John of Reading|talk]]) 20:37, 7 May 2014 (UTC)
::It still doesn't for me on FF29. What I don't understand is that clicking on [[Wikipedia:Notability (sports)#Motorsports]] ''does'' take me to the right place, but clicking [[WP:NMOTORSPORT]], which has exactly that as its target, ''doesn't''. If it is a browser problem, wouldn't they both be wrong? [[User:JohnCD|JohnCD]] ([[User talk:JohnCD|talk]]) 22:06, 7 May 2014 (UTC)
:::Works for me in Safari, but not with FF 29. With FF it does jump to a spot in the page pretty quickly, perhaps before it's read and dealt with all the stylesheets and JS that affects the page - i.e. as {{U|John of Reading}} is suggesting. The delta between where it lands and where it should land is also about that size.--<small>[[User:JohnBlackburne|JohnBlackburne]]</small><sup>[[User_talk:JohnBlackburne|words]]</sup><sub style="margin-left:-2.0ex;">[[Special:Contributions/JohnBlackburne|deeds]]</sub> 22:19, 7 May 2014 (UTC)
::::It's a [[race condition]], something encountered in asynchronous processing. You've got two (well, actually a ''lot'' more) largely-unrelated tasks being kicked off more or less at the same time: one to go to the position specified by the fragment <code>#Motorsports</code>, the other to collapse the FAQ box at the top. If the collapse finishes first, the position will be correct; if the collapse finishes second, the position will be off by the height reduction of the FAQ box. Which one finishes first varies not just between browsers, but between machines with the same browser - it can be affected by other things going on unrelated to browsing, like that big spreadsheet that you're printing off for Joe in Accounts. --[[User:Redrose64|<span style="color:#a80000; background:#ffeeee; text-decoration:inherit">Red</span>rose64]] ([[User talk:Redrose64|talk]]) 23:16, 7 May 2014 (UTC)
::::This might (or might not!) have something to do with HotCat or WikEd. See [[User talk:Cacycle/wikEd#wikEd bug report:clicking on section links]]. [[User:Thincat|Thincat]] ([[User talk:Thincat|talk]]) 22:15, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
:::::The wikEd/HotCat problem being discussed below at [[#Section links not working properly]] has got nothing to do with FF 29 as that also occurs on FF 28. Also, [[User:JohnBlackburne|JohnBlackburne]]'s description above doesn't fit the symptoms of the wikEd/HotCat incompatibility: here, it appears the browser jumps to nearly the right place, whereas with the wikEd/HotCat problem, you first get to the right place and then suddenly land at the top of the page. The "nearly getting there" effect is most probably what [[User:Redrose64|Redrose64]] explained above. The "jump to top" effect is a conflict between wikEd and HotCat. [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 22:32, 9 May 2014 (UTC)
:I've just upgraded from FF 28 to 29.0.1 and I think that the behaviour ''has'' changed. --[[User:Redrose64|<span style="color:#a80000; background:#ffeeee; text-decoration:inherit">Red</span>rose64]] ([[User talk:Redrose64|talk]]) 10:47, 10 May 2014 (UTC)
:: Concur. I've got FF28 on my desktop and FF29 on my laptop, and it works on the former but not the latter. [[User:Black Kite|Black Kite]] ([[User talk:Black Kite|talk]]) 10:59, 10 May 2014 (UTC)
:Question: shouldn't the collapsing JS take care of that? If window.scroll != 0 and the top position of the elements to be collapsed is < window.scroll, then the collapsing script should adjust window.scroll appropriately. [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 12:28, 16 May 2014 (UTC)
::The thing is, how will it know whether the jump-to-anchor has already been acted upon or not? --[[User:Redrose64|<span style="color:#a80000; background:#ffeeee; text-decoration:inherit">Red</span>rose64]] ([[User talk:Redrose64|talk]]) 19:15, 16 May 2014 (UTC)
:::I would suppose (but didn't test it) that the "jump to anchor" has been done if window.scroll != 0. [[User:Lupo|Lupo]] 09:09, 17 May 2014 (UTC)

== Privacy policy changing ==

