***There is a huge difference between "[http://blog.wikimedia.org/2014/05/16/anonymous-editor-acquisition/ Inviting anonymous editors to join the Wikipedia community]" (as linked below by John of Reading) and nagging them into it. The suggestion that IP editors should just "permanently fix" the annoyance by creating account is, imo, indefensible. Use of annoyance tactics like that would seem to me to conflict heavily with the right to edit Wikipedia in gf as an IP, as recently also enshrined in the new Privacy Policy. [[Special:Contributions/86.181.67.132|86.181.67.132]] ([[User talk:86.181.67.132|talk]]) 17:38, 20 May 2014 (UTC)

