::::::::::::several comments: 
::::::::::::# search and replace is neutralized in IE for ~a year now, even though the button was still visible for some or all of this time (don't have access to IE, so i'm not sure if it's visible now). when the button was/is visible, it just does nothing in IE. 
::::::::::::#{{re|Peridon}} you *can* test monobook when logged out: just add "?useskin=monobook" to the end of the address line. if there's already a question mark in the address line (true when editing), replace the "?" with "&".
::::::::::::# it seems that the search and replace is broken, at least in chrome: what i mean is, it works erroneously. superficial tests show that "replace all" works fine, but "replace" can do wrong things, depending whether there is any selected text in the article, and maybe also depending on caret location. similar issues with IE are what made the developers neutralize this button in IE. this tool's code is pretty ugly (sorry if anyone is offended), and i'm sure is someone will create a nice search/replace module the developers will be happy to adopt it.
